We need to escape the double quotes in line3 (around GMT) and also in line16 (date.toString() returns a string, but we are not writing quotes). Actually, date.toString() is a method call, no quotes. Also line21: new Date() is fine. So only line3 has double quotes.

But also we have double quotes in the Java code for string literals? None else. So we escape those.

Thus line3 becomes:         TimeZone tz = TimeZone.getTimeZone(\\\"GMT\\\");\n

Now we combine all lines into one string with \n escapes.

Also we need to escape any backslash we use. For example, if we write \\\" in the JSON string, that means we want to represent a backslash followed by a double quote. In the JSON string, we need to write \\\\\" because: to get a backslash character, we need \\, and then a double quote we need \", but since the double quote is inside a JSON string, we need to escape it as \". So actually, to represent a single backslash followed by a double quote, we need to write: \\\\\". Because: backslash is escaped as \\, double quote is escaped as \". So sequence: backslash (represented as \\), double quote (represented as \") -> \\\". But wait, we want the string content to be \". So we need to write \" in the JSON string. That's just \". So for a literal backslash in the string, we need \\, and for a literal double quote, we need \". So the sequence \" is represented as \\\". So if we want the string to contain \", we write \". So for the Java source we want getTimeZone(\"GMT\"), which in the JSON string we need to write getTimeZone(\"GMT\"). So we replace " with \". That's all. So we don't need extra backslashes for the backslash. Because the Java source does not contain a backslash before the quote; it contains a double quote character. When we write JSON, we escape that double quote with a backslash. So we simply write \". So line3 in the JSON string becomes:         TimeZone tz = TimeZone.getTimeZone(\"GMT\");\n. But wait, that would put a backslash before the double quote in the JSON text. So indeed we write \" as \". So we need to put a backslash before each double quote inside the string.

